On Wednesday, February 24, 2010, at 07:43PM, "David Schwarze" <dschwarze(-at-)dfwair.net> wrote:

>I experienced one engine failure that fits your description many 
>years ago.  When I tore down the engine it turned out to be a dropped 
>valve - the engine was a total loss

Bob,

Some valve failures are noisy, others occur silently.

Pull the spark plugs. If a valve stem failed and the head fell off, you'll know it by the look of the end of the spark plug.

If the plug won't come out, that could be another indicator.

